# Always Use Dot Shorthands

Prefer dot shorthand syntax (`.foo`) over fully qualified names (`Type.foo`) whenever the context type is clear to the compiler. Reference: https://dart.dev/language/dot-shorthands

## Enum values

```dart
// BAD
Status currentStatus = Status.running;

// GOOD
Status currentStatus = .running;
```

## Switch expressions and cases

```dart
// BAD
return switch (level) {
  LogLevel.debug => 'gray',
  LogLevel.error => 'red',
};

// GOOD
return switch (level) {
  .debug => 'gray',
  .error => 'red',
};
```

## Named and factory constructors

```dart
// BAD
Point origin = Point.origin();

// GOOD
Point origin = .origin();
```

## Unnamed constructors via `.new`

```dart
// BAD
final ScrollController _scrollController = ScrollController();
Map<String, bool> flags = <String, bool>{};

// GOOD
final ScrollController _scrollController = .new();
Map<String, bool> flags = .new();
```

## Static members

```dart
// BAD
int port = int.parse('8080');
BigInt zero = BigInt.zero;

// GOOD
int port = .parse('8080');
BigInt zero = .zero;
```

## Equality checks (shorthand on the right-hand side)

```dart
// BAD
if (myColor == Color.green) { ... }

// GOOD
if (myColor == .green) { ... }
```
